      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that those are the classics, but i'm looking for something more current. like, if i was walking through a hood in a major city today, how would i tell the difference between regular street style and what people call \"urban\" style? what are the specific traits, like fabrics or silhouettes, that link a certain look to those specific urban/minority communities? i just don't want to accidentally design something that feels \"white\" or \"mainstream\" when i'm trying to capture that specific vibe.",
